{"id":20,"idInBook":1175,"chapterId":47,"bookId":15,"arabic":"حَدَّثَنَا قَبِيصَةُ، قَالَ‏:‏ حَدَّثَنَا سُفْيَانُ، عَنِ الأَعْمَشِ، عَنْ أَبِي صَالِحٍ، عَنِ ابْنِ عُمَرَ قَالَ‏:‏ إِذَا كَانُوا أَرْبَعَةً فَلا بَأْسَ‏.‏","english":{"narrator":"","text":"Ibn 'Umar said, \"When there are four, there is no harm.\""},"hadithNumber":1175,"hadithId":20,"reference":"47:20","meta":{"id":"aladab_almufrad","length":1326,"totalChapters":57,"arabic":{"title":"الأدب المفرد","author":"الإمام محمد بن إسماعيل البخاري"},"english":{"title":"Al-Adab Al-Mufrad","author":"Imam Muhammad ibn Ismail al-Bukhari"}},"chapter":{"id":47,"bookId":15,"arabic":"كتاب تعامل الناس","english":"Behaviour with people","startHadith":1156,"endHadith":1177,"totalHadiths":22},"version":{"name":"aladab_almufrad","title":"Al-Adab Al-Mufrad","chapters":57}}